Model name is singular and is same as the downcase of class name and follows snake case.
Every model maps to a table and table name will be plural. For ex:- category is the model and categories is the model.
Every model will have it's own respective controller with the plural of the model name followed by _controller. Ex:- category model will have categories_controller
Every controller will have its own view folder. Ex:- categories_controller will have its own category dir in views.
Every action defined inside the controller will have its own view file.
Instance variables defined inside an action of a controller available only to it's viewfile.
Ever table will always have it's primary key called as id, which will be an integer and set to auto incriment.
Foregin key should be model name _ id